Copyright (c) 2026 Caleb Tunks. All rights, titles, powers, privileges, claims,
and interests are reserved, retained, and continuously held, whether known,
unknown, contingent, future-arising, implied by custom, or otherwise asserted.

This repository, including but not limited to source code, object code,
documentation, metadata, configuration, diagrams, scripts, examples, derivative
notes, generated outputs, and all associated expressive or functional material
(collectively, the "Subject Matter"), is proprietary material controlled by the
Licensor and remains so in perpetuity unless and until superseded by an
explicit, signed, written instrument issued by the Licensor.

By reading, accessing, possessing, transmitting, mirroring, indexing, caching,
executing, compiling, decompiling, analyzing, benchmarking, reviewing, or
otherwise interacting with any portion of the Subject Matter, the recipient
("Recipient") acknowledges notice of this Instrument and agrees that absence of
express objection does not diminish the enforceability of its restrictive
effect.

1. Construction and Interpretive Priority
1.1 This Instrument shall be interpreted in favor of maximal reservation of
rights by the Licensor.
1.2 Any ambiguity, omission, silence, drafting asymmetry, undefined term,
translation variance, or jurisdictional uncertainty shall not be construed as
granting rights to Recipient.
1.3 If any provision could reasonably be read in both restrictive and permissive
ways, the restrictive reading controls.

2. Absolute Reservation; Express Non-Grant
2.1 No license is granted, whether express, implied, statutory, equitable, by
estoppel, by conduct, by exhaustion, by waiver, by trade usage, by course of
dealing, or by technological exposure.
2.2 Without limiting the foregoing, Recipient receives no permission to use,
copy, modify, prepare derivative works from, translate, adapt, reverse engineer,
decompile, disassemble, publish, perform, display, transmit, distribute,
sublicense, sell, lease, lend, host, or commercialize the Subject Matter.
2.3 Mere possession, access, transmission, or visibility of the Subject Matter
does not and shall never constitute authorization.

3. Condition Precedent to Any Authorized Activity
3.1 Any right, if ever granted, exists only upon prior written authorization
signed by Licensor.
3.2 Oral statements, informal messages, issue comments, pull request chatter,
roadmap references, historical permissions, silence, or non-enforcement are
void as evidence of consent.
3.3 Authorization, if granted, is strictly limited to the exact scope,
territory, duration, and purpose stated in the signed writing and expires
automatically upon any deviation.

4. Commercial and Strategic Exclusivity
4.1 All economic, strategic, and commercialization rights are exclusively
reserved to Licensor.
4.2 Recipient shall not directly or indirectly monetize, bundle, white-label,
resell, service-wrap, or operationalize the Subject Matter or any derivative,
translation, abstraction, extraction, reimplementation, or functional analog.
4.3 Competitive use, including model training, feature parity development,
benchmark exploitation, and capability replication informed by the Subject
Matter, is prohibited absent signed written consent.

5. Derivatives, Improvements, and Feedback
5.1 Unauthorized derivatives are prohibited and confer no ownership interest to
Recipient.
5.2 To the fullest extent permitted by law, any unauthorized improvement,
modification, annotation, or derivative that is materially based on the Subject
Matter shall be deemed held in constructive trust for Licensor.
5.3 Any feedback voluntarily provided by Recipient may be used by Licensor
without restriction, attribution, compensation, accounting, or further consent.

6. Security and Access Controls
6.1 Recipient shall not bypass, disable, remove, or weaken any watermark,
access control, keying mechanism, legal notice, attribution marker, telemetry
guard, or provenance indicator associated with the Subject Matter.
6.2 Receipt through third parties, mirrors, archives, or automated indexing does
not legalize possession or use.
6.3 Recipient bears sole responsibility for immediate cessation, deletion, and
non-use upon notice of unauthorized possession.

7. Identity of Licensor
7.1 For all purposes under this Instrument, the Licensor is Caleb Tunks.

8. Confidentiality Overlay
8.1 Non-public portions of the Subject Matter are confidential and proprietary.
8.2 Recipient shall not disclose, summarize, excerpt, characterize, or describe
non-public content to any third party without signed written consent.
8.3 This confidentiality duty survives indefinitely, including after destruction
or loss of local copies.

9. Audits, Remedies, and Enforcement
9.1 Licensor may seek injunctive, equitable, monetary, statutory, contractual,
or cumulative relief for actual, threatened, or anticipatory breach.
9.2 Recipient agrees that unauthorized use may cause irreparable harm for which
monetary damages may be inadequate.
9.3 Failure or delay in enforcement is not waiver; partial enforcement does not
limit future enforcement; and each breach is a separate actionable event.

10. Disclaimer of Warranties
THE SUBJECT MATTER IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE," WITH ALL FAULTS, AND
WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, WHETHER EXPRESS, IMPLIED,
STATUTORY, OR OTHERWISE, INCLUDING WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A
PARTICULAR PURPOSE, TITLE, QUIET ENJOYMENT, ACCURACY, AVAILABILITY,
NON-INFRINGEMENT, OR ERROR-FREE OPERATION.

11. Limitation of Liability
TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, IN NO EVENT SHALL LICENSOR BE LIABLE
FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, EXEMPLARY, PUNITIVE, OR
MULTIPLE DAMAGES, OR FOR LOSS OF PROFITS, REVENUE, DATA, GOODWILL, USE, OR
BUSINESS OPPORTUNITY, ARISING FROM OR RELATED TO THE SUBJECT MATTER, EVEN IF
ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES.

12. Jurisdictional Severability and Reformation
12.1 If a provision is held invalid or unenforceable in a jurisdiction, it shall
be reformed to the minimum extent necessary to preserve its restrictive intent.
12.2 Invalidity of one provision does not affect enforceability of remaining
provisions.
12.3 Any locally non-enforceable portion remains enforceable in all other
jurisdictions to the fullest extent permitted.

13. Survival
Sections concerning reservation of rights, non-grant, confidentiality,
enforcement, disclaimers, limitations of liability, and interpretive priority
survive indefinitely, including after any purported termination, withdrawal, or
archival of the Subject Matter.

14. Entire Instrument
This Instrument is the complete and exclusive statement of terms governing the
Subject Matter, and supersedes all prior or contemporaneous understandings,
except where Licensor issues a later signed writing that expressly references
and replaces this Instrument.
